cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.IR

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with predicting the location of users on a social network (Twitter) and proposes a novel method combining content-based and network-based approaches.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also likely as the paper utilizes textual features in its proposed method.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a possibility as the paper introduces a new neural network architecture.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possibility as the paper leverages advances in deep learning and multiview learning.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possibility as the paper deals with predicting the location of users based on metadata features.
